Eragrostis trichodes

   [5749.jpg]
    Authority   (Nutt.) Wood
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5749

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION: It is a warm seasoned, bunch grass reaching 60-120
   cm in height. It produces a heavy fibrous root system and spreads by
   seed and rooting at the nodes. USE: A palatable grass popular as an
   ornamental. It is highly palatable to cattle and wildlife and must be
   managed to avoid overgrazing of shorter than 13-20 cm. GROWING PERIOD:
   Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Sand love grass.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 371 [USE, TEXT, DRA, FER]
   Duke J 1979 pp 95 [TEMP, RAIN, PH]
   Duke J 1975 pp 16 [TEMP, RAIN, PH]

